\pard\b\f0\fs25\sa220 Appendix A.7: Clinician Routes\par
\pard\i\f0\fs20\sa100 File Path: backend/routes/clinician.js\par
\pard\i\f0\fs20\sa100 Section Description: Patient lookup, records management, and appointment handling for clinicians.\par
\pard\f0\fs20\sa100 What this file does: This file implements the clinical workflow endpoints used by authorised healthcare staff.\par
\pard\f0\fs20\sa100 How this file is used in the system: It is called by the clinician dashboard to retrieve assigned work summaries, browse patients, inspect a full patient file, create and update medical records, schedule appointments, and change appointment status.\par
\pard\b\f0\fs20\sa120 Main responsibilities implemented in this file:\par
\pard\f0\fs19\li360\sa70 - Allows clinicians and admins to access the clinician route group.\par
\pard\f0\fs19\li360\sa70 - Returns dashboard metrics such as patient counts, appointments, and recently attended patients.\par
\pard\f0\fs19\li360\sa70 - Provides detailed patient lookup including profile, records, and appointment history.\par
\pard\f0\fs19\li360\sa70 - Creates new medical records and checks ownership before record updates are allowed.\par
\pard\f0\fs19\li360\sa70 - Schedules appointments and enforces valid appointment status transitions.\par
\pard\sa120\par
