\pard\i\f0\fs20\sa100 File Path: backend/routes/patient.js\par
\pard\i\f0\fs20\sa100 Section Description: Patient profile, appointments, records, and summary endpoints.\par
\pard\f0\fs20\sa100 What this file does: This file provides the self-service backend interface through which patients can safely access only their own data.\par
\pard\f0\fs20\sa100 How this file is used in the system: It is consumed by the patient dashboard to load the current user profile, personal medical records, personal appointments, and a summary view containing recent visits, upcoming appointments, and active medications.\par
\pard\b\f0\fs20\sa120 Main responsibilities implemented in this file:\par
\pard\f0\fs19\li360\sa70 - Restricts the whole route group to authenticated users with the patient role.\par
\pard\f0\fs19\li360\sa70 - Returns only the current patient\u\u\us profile and associated health data.\par
\pard\f0\fs19\li360\sa70 - Prevents cross-patient data exposure by always querying with req.user.id.\par
\pard\f0\fs19\li360\sa70 - Aggregates summary metrics used on the patient home page.\par
\pard\sa120\par
\pard\b\f0\fs20\sa120 Full source code listing:\par
