\pard\f0\fs20\sa100 How this file is used in the system: It is used by npm during installation and execution of the backend. It documents the packages needed for routing, database access, password hashing, JWT handling, logging, and environment configuration.\par
\pard\b\f0\fs20\sa120 Main responsibilities implemented in this file:\par
\pard\f0\fs19\li360\sa70 - Declares the backend entry point and package identity.\par
\pard\f0\fs19\li360\sa70 - Defines runtime scripts for starting and developing the Node.js server.\par
\pard\f0\fs19\li360\sa70 - Lists the core dependencies that support the RBAC EHR implementation.\par
